      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TIME TO DANCE NZ (3) has been racing consistently since winning at Newcastle last month, coming from a very wide barrier for fourth last start at Menangle. Has the benefit of a good draw and is proven at this circuit and distance so looks well placed. ROCKET ME (9) came from wider on this row to win at Dubbo two runs ago before finishing second at his latest appearance at Young. Can travel in a nice spot from this draw and wait on the sprint lane if necessary. Contender. SUNSET JAY JAY (10) drew very wide last week but was a close third in the city prior and scored at this circuit and distance last month so is worth another chance. TULHURST TIMMY (6) returns off some decent efforts at Albion Park including a close second from the back row. Won the last time he raced here. Go well.",
